          </p>
          <p>
            This point in time is known as the <strong>Unix Epoch</strong>. It was chosen somewhat arbitrarily but has since become the bedrock of global computing. Every file creation, system log, and network packet today carries a legacy born from those early days of mainframe computing.
          </p>
        </div>
