            <p>
              On <strong>January 19, 2038, at 03:14:07 UTC</strong>, 32-bit systems will overflow and wrap around to a negative number, effectively "resetting" time to 1901. Modern 64-bit systems have already solved this, pushing the "end of time" billions of years into the future.
            </p>
